      prompt: `The Mars Perseverance rover is a robot designed to collect samples of rock and soil. During an experiment, the rover moves at a constant speed on a straight path toward a designated target. The equation <em>y</em> = 390 &minus; 142<em>x</em> gives the rover&rsquo;s remaining distance from its target <em>y</em>, in meters, <em>x</em> hours after the start of the experiment. What is the best interpretation of 390 in this context?`,
